codex
The first local cluster attempts hit the previously documented sandbox limitation: PostgreSQL 14’s bootstrap process tries a SysV shared-memory allocation before a configuration file exists. I’m checking the installed server’s supported startup controls and official PostgreSQL behavior for a safe mmap-only bootstrap; this is acceptance-critical, so I will not substitute skipped tests.
